<paragraph id="7B4E368D2101FF95B1DCFE858A8CFE35" blockId="6.[163,1070,355,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">
Comment: 
<taxonomicName id="BCF14D0E2101FF95B02AFE828A42FEF8" authorityName="ZHENG" authorityYear="1988" box="[341,530,356,377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tortile">
<emphasis id="4985EA9F2101FF95B02AFE828A42FEF8" box="[341,530,356,377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Lobrathium tortile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had previously been recorded from 
<collectingRegion id="B935F86F2101FF95B2F5FE858C7AFEF8" box="[906,1066,355,377]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Shaanxi, Hubei</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="B935F86F2101FF95B1B1FE67894FFE16" box="[206,287,385,407]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F604B7C2101FF95B051FE6789E9FE16" author="ASSING V" box="[302,441,385,407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="197" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref8487" refString="ASSING V. (2012): A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 61 (1): 49 - 128." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING 2012</bibRefCitation>
); the currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="E3CA2A082101FF95B2C8FE678BABFE16" box="[951,1019,385,407]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="6.[163,208,1294,1314]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,692,1275]" captionTargetId="figure-241@6.[163,1069,692,1275]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Map 1: Distributions of Lobrathium tortile ZHENG (diamonds), L. emeimontis nov.sp. (circle), and L. dabaicum nov.sp. (triangle) in China." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5412849/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Map 1</figureCitation>
. The specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="B935F86F2101FF95B0F1FE78899FFE35" box="[398,463,414,436]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="6" pageNumber="197">Gansu</collectingRegion>
in July are mostly teneral.
</paragraph>
